  "overview": {
    "value": "Tianlong-2 is a three-stage, small-lift launch vehicle developed by Space Pioneer that uses liquid oxygen and kerosene as propellants for its first two stages. It is 32.8 m tall, 3.35 m in diameter, and can lift 2,000 kg to low Earth orbit or 1,500 kg to a 500 km sun-synchronous orbit. Its only flight to date, on 2 April 2023, succeeded, making it China's first privately-developed liquid-fueled rocket to reach orbit.",
